    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A variant on traditional electrophoresis, capillary electrophoresis (CE) is designed to separate particles by species. A sample is placed in a capillary tube subjected to a high-voltage charge which separates the constituent ions by differences in size, shape, and charge.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
